title: Winfield-Mt. Union falls in first round to Notre Dame
text:
Winfield-Mt. Union falls in first round to Notre Dame Oct 21, 2015 
BY ANDY KRUTSINGER 
Mt. Pleasant News 
WINFIELD â€” The Winfield-Mt. Union volleyball team was eliminated from postseason play on Tuesday night with a 3-0 (25-20, 26-24 and 25-14) loss to Notre Dame. The Wolves fought the Nikes hard in the first couple of sets, but two close wins and a pull-away in the third was enough to send Notre Dame to the second round. 
Pearl Krieger-Coble led the Wolves with seven kills in the first round matchup. Cassidy Lennie and Lexee Hartsock each had four, Lauren Jamison had three and Hannah Buffington had two. The leading assister was Caitlin Jamison, with 17. 
Lennie had a big day serving, going 14-14, with one ace. L. Jamison was 7-7, with two aces; Krieger-Coble went 6-6; C. Jamison was 8-10 with three aces; Sophie Kongable was 10-10 with an ace; Kara Wade was 8-9 with one ace; and Kenzie Scott was 3-4. 
Defensively, Kongable led the team with 21 digs. Lennie had 15; C. Jamison had 14; Wade had 13; L. Jamison had 10; Scott finished with six; Krieger Coble had one; and Buffington finished with three. 
The Wolves finished their season with a 17-16 overall record, which included a 6-3 record in conference. Notre Dame moved on to play WACO in the second round, which takes place Tuesday, Oct. 27, at 7 p.m.
